Sprint Review:

What did you learn from doing our first sprint?
We learned how to apply Agile and Scrum in a real project setting, including breaking down user stories into management tasks, using Trello to track our progress, and communicating regularly as a team. We also gained experience balancing design and implementation within a short period of time.
What did go well? Why?
Task delegation went well because responsibilities were clearly assigned to each team member. This helped us stay organized and ensured that work was completed efficiently without too much overlap.
What didn’t go well? Why not?
The start of the sprint was slower than expected because there was a lot to organize and keep track of (charts, tasks, tools, etc.). This delayed momentum early on and led to a heavier workload toward the end of the sprint.
How can you make things better next time?
For our next sprint, we plan to get organized more efficiently, define our necessary tasks and deliverables, and start the process earlier. For this sprint, we had a hard time defining all of our objectives in the initial stages so we will ensure this is done sooner and we aren’t rushed towards the end of the sprint. 
Are you satisfied with what you already completed?
Yes, we are satisfied with what we completed during this sprint, as we were able to design and implement the core pages of our website.
Which group was invited? What are your observations/notes? Everybody was present?
We invited Group 6 to our sprint review. Everyone was present, and the session went smoothly. We were able to clearly demonstrate our progress and explain our design decisions, and they provided helpful feedback for moving forward.


